      "correct_choice": "c",
      "rationale": "<p>Choice C is correct. The mean of a data set is found by dividing the sum of the values in the data set by the number of values in the data set. Therefore, the mean of data set A is <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"the fraction with numerator 72, plus 73, plus 73, plus 76, plus 76, and denominator 5\"></span>, which simplifies to 74. The mean of data set B is represented by the equation <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"the fraction with numerator 61, plus 64, plus 74, plus 85, plus x, and denominator 5\"></span>, or <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"the fraction with numerator 284 plus x, and denominator 5\"></span>. It&rsquo;s given that the mean of data set A is equal to the mean of data set B. Therefore, the equation <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"74 equals, the fraction with numerator 284 plus x, and denominator 5\"></span> can be used to solve for <span class=\"italic\">x</span>. Multiplying both sides of this equation by 5 yields <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"370 equals, 284 plus x\"></span>. Subtracting 284 from both sides of this equation yields <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"86 equals x\"></span>.<p>Choices A, B, and D are incorrect and may result from calculation errors.</p></p>\n"
